{%- liquid
  assign whatsapp_number = section.settings.whatsapp_number | default: '917337294499'
  assign whatsapp_text = 'Hello Golden Collections, I need help measuring my deity idol for jewellery size.' | url_encode
-%}

<section class="gc-size-guide color-{{ section.settings.color_scheme }}">
  <div class="page-width">
    <nav class="gc-size-guide__breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="{{ routes.root_url }}">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span>Size Guide</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="gc-size-guide__hero">
      <div>
        <p class="gc-size-guide__eyebrow">{{ section.settings.eyebrow }}</p>
        <h1>{{ section.settings.heading }}</h1>
        <p>{{ section.settings.subheading }}</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gc-size-guide__hero-actions">
        <a class="gc-size-guide__button" href="#crowns">Measure crowns</a>
        <a class="gc-size-guide__button gc-size-guide__button--secondary" href="https://wa.me/{{ whatsapp_number }}?text={{ whatsapp_text }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          WhatsApp size help
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="gc-size-guide__quick">
      <article>
        <strong>1. Measure the idol first</strong>
        <span>Idol height and placement area decide the likely ornament size.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>2. Check product photos</strong>
        <span>Use the product measurement-tape images before ordering.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>3. Ask if unsure</strong>
        <span>Send idol photos and measurements on WhatsApp for help.</span>
      </article>
    </div>

    <nav class="gc-size-guide__nav" aria-label="Size guide sections">
      <a href="#crowns">Crowns</a>
      <a href="#necklaces">Necklaces and harams</a>
      <a href="#vaddanam">Vaddanam</a>
      <a href="#earrings">Earrings</a>
      <a href="#videos">Videos</a>
    </nav>

    <section id="crowns" class="gc-size-guide__section">
      <div class="gc-size-guide__section-head">
        <p>Crown sizing guide</p>
        <h2>Crowns need different measurements for open-back and full-round styles.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="gc-size-guide__grid gc-size-guide__grid--two">
        <article class="gc-size-guide__measure-card">
          <div class="gc-size-guide__diagram" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 240 180" role="img">
              <path d="M84 76c8-34 64-34 72 0l7 33c5 28-15 52-43 52s-48-24-43-52l7-33z" fill="#fff8ea" stroke="#8f5f11" stroke-width="4"/>
              <path d="M72 76h96" stroke="#8f1f18" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M72 76l14-10M72 76l14 10M168 76l-14-10M168 76l-14 10" stroke="#8f1f18" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <text x="120" y="38" text-anchor="middle">Ear to ear</text>
              <text x="120" y="166" text-anchor="middle">Open-back / half crown</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Half crown or open-back crown</h3>
            <p>Measure the head or face width from one side to the other. For many idols this means the space where the crown will sit, often ear-to-ear or side-to-side.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Use: head width, inner crown width, crown height.</li>
              <li>Best for: crowns that do not go fully around the head.</li>
              <li>Tip: product photos usually show width and height with a tape.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="gc-size-guide__measure-card">
          <div class="gc-size-guide__diagram" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 240 180" role="img">
              <ellipse cx="120" cy="89" rx="58" ry="68" fill="#fff8ea" stroke="#8f5f11" stroke-width="4"/>
              <path d="M120 22c42 5 74 32 74 67s-32 62-74 67c-42-5-74-32-74-67s32-62 74-67z" fill="none" stroke="#8f1f18" stroke-width="5" stroke-dasharray="10 8"/>
              <path d="M194 89l-11-9M194 89l-11 9" stroke="#8f1f18" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <text x="120" y="20" text-anchor="middle">Full circumference</text>
              <text x="120" y="166" text-anchor="middle">Full-round crown</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Full-round crown</h3>
            <p>Measure around the idol head where the crown will sit. This is the circumference. Do not use only front width for a full-round crown.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Use: full circumference, crown height, idol height.</li>
              <li>Best for: crowns that wrap around the head.</li>
              <li>Tip: keep the tape level around the head.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="necklaces" class="gc-size-guide__section">
      <div class="gc-size-guide__section-head">
        <p>Necklace and haram sizing</p>
        <h2>Decide where the ornament should sit on the idol.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="gc-size-guide__grid">
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Short necklace</h3>
          <p>Measure the neck or upper chest width. Check product width and chain/drop length.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Short necklace</h3>
          <p>Measure from neck to the upper chest where the necklace should end.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Long haram</h3>
          <p>Measure from neck to the lower chest or waist area depending on the desired look.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="vaddanam" class="gc-size-guide__section">
      <div class="gc-size-guide__section-head">
        <p>Waist ornaments</p>
        <h2>For vaddanam, measure the waist placement area.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="gc-size-guide__grid gc-size-guide__grid--two">
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Front vaddanam look</h3>
          <p>Measure the front width across the idol waist where the belt should be visible.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Full waist fit</h3>
          <p>Measure the complete waist circumference if the ornament needs to wrap around.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="earrings" class="gc-size-guide__section">
      <div class="gc-size-guide__section-head">
        <p>Earrings and accessories</p>
        <h2>Use the idol face size and exact placement area.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="gc-size-guide__grid">
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Earrings</h3>
          <p>Measure the side face area and check product height so the earring does not look too large.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Nose rings and face accessories</h3>
          <p>Measure the exact face placement and compare with product measurement photos.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="gc-size-guide__simple-card">
          <h3>Weapons and alankaram accessories</h3>
          <p>Measure the hand, shoulder, or setup area where the accessory will be placed.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="videos" class="gc-size-guide__section gc-size-guide__videos">
      <div class="gc-size-guide__section-head">
        <p>Video examples</p>
        <h2>We can add short measuring videos here.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="gc-size-guide__video-grid">
        <article>
          <span>Coming next</span>
          <h3>How to measure an open-back crown</h3>
          <p>Animated guide now, real idol video can be added later.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Coming next</span>
          <h3>How to measure a full-round crown</h3>
          <p>Show tape around the full head circumference.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Upload option</span>
          <h3>Use your live videos later</h3>
          <p>You can upload real explanation videos and we can add captions, labels, and voiceover.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="gc-size-guide__section gc-size-guide__faq">
      <div class="gc-size-guide__section-head">
        <p>Common questions</p>
        <h2>Quick answers before ordering</h2>
      </div>
      <details>
        <summary>What if I do not know my idol size?</summary>
        <p>Start with idol height. If possible, take one front photo with a scale or measuring tape next to the idol.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do I need all crown measurements?</summary>
        <p>No. Open-back crowns mainly need head width and crown height. Full-round crowns need circumference.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can Golden Collections help check size?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Share idol photos and measurements on WhatsApp before ordering.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>
</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I measure a deity idol for an open-back crown?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Measure the head or face width from one side to the other where the crown will sit, often ear-to-ear or side-to-side."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I measure a deity idol for a full-round crown?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Measure the full circumference around the idol head where the crown will sit."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What if I am not sure about deity jewellery size?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Check product measurement photos and share idol photos with measurements on WhatsApp for size help before ordering."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
</script>

<style>
  .gc-size-guide {
    background: #fffaf0;
    color: #21180d;
    padding: 1.4rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__breadcrumb {
    color: #6f6254;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 1.18rem;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__breadcrumb a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.3rem;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__eyebrow,
  .gc-size-guide__section-head p,
  .gc-size-guide__video-grid span {
    color: #8f5f11;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .gc-size-guide h1,
  .gc-size-guide h2,
  .gc-size-guide h3 {
    color: #1f170d;
    font-family: 'New York', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .gc-size-guide h1 {
    font-size: 3.8rem;
    line-height: 1.02;
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__hero p:not(.gc-size-guide__eyebrow) {
    color: #4e4438;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    line-height: 1.42;
    margin: 0.85rem 0 0;
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__hero-actions {
    align-items: start;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__button {
    align-items: center;
    background: #8f1f18;
    border: 1px solid #8f1f18;
    border-radius: 6px;
    color: #ffffff;
    display: inline-flex;
    font-size: 1.24rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    min-height: 44px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__button--secondary {
    background: #fffdf8;
    border-color: rgba(151, 99, 16, 0.24);
    color: #8f1f18;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__quick,
  .gc-size-guide__grid,
  .gc-size-guide__video-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.8rem;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__quick {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .gc-size-guide__quick article,
  .gc-size-guide__measure-card,
